How many categories do editors typically participate in?
This program uses the output from 'buildPageCategories.pl'
to identify what categories authors participate in.


You should have "page2rootcat.txt" in this directory.

Run it as:

gunzip -c /Volumes/LucaWikiMac/sortedstats/enwiki-20070206/enwiki-20070206-allsorted.stats.gz | ./convert-old2new.pl | ./compile-user2rootcat.pl > user-categories.txt

To build build histograms of how broadly users
explore when editing pages, I ran the following:
   70  ./histogram.pl 4 user-categories-text.txt > hist-totalcats.txt
   73  ./histogram.pl 6 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part25.txt
   74  ./histogram.pl 8 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part33.txt
   75  ./histogram.pl 10 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part50.txt
   76  ./histogram.pl 12 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part66.txt
   77  ./histogram.pl 14 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part75.txt
   78  ./histogram.pl 16 user-categories-text.txt > hist-part90.txt

